        "body": "You don't accidentally lead the league in wins, points, and Prestige. Jack was <strong>that dude in the late 2010s</strong> — back-to-back titles, the league's first dynasty. But the last few years? Injuries, bad luck, and near-misses. Still, he's five Prestige points clear of Kyle, clinging to the GOAT throne, and about to become the first to hit 15,000 regular season points. At some point, the bouncebacks come. The injuries stop. The stars align. And the legend reminds you why he became a legend in the first place. <strong>Jack's not done — he's reloading.</strong>"
